data.title: Carl L. LeNoble Obituary 2023

data.text:
Carl L. LeNoble, age 87 from Clintonville WI, passed away on Friday, December 15, 2023 at Cherry Meadows Hospice. Carl was born in Clintonville on July 1, 1936, son of William and Imogene (Geer) LeNoble.

Carl served in the U.S. Army from 1955-1958. He was stationed overseas where he would reminisce about playing football with his Army Squad. He was Honorably Discharged.

When Carl came back home he worked a few jobs before settling with Steinberg (H&S) for the remainder of his working years until his retirement.

Carl is survived by his 3 children: Lisa (Bill) Derby, Scott LeNoble (Roxanne Maddix), Jessica (David) Moderson; 6 grandchildren: Kira Hohn, Tiffany Maddix, Cassandra (Tyler) Gehrdes, Jennifer (Jeremiah) Elandt, Kristina (Jeff) Runge, Elizabeth (Andrew) Pitsch; 9 great grandchildren: Aloura, Lily, Savanna, Azailia, Sebastian, Alyssa, Taylor, Olivia, Owen; 7 brothers and sisters: Rogene Wussow, Victor (Sue) LeNoble, Judy Wudstrack, Theresa Bork, Mike LeNoble, Debbie (Mark) Wenzelow, Nancy (Tom) Young. Carl is further survived by numerous nieces, nephews, other relatives and friends.

He is preceeded in death by a brother, James LeNoble; 2 sisters, Marcella Malliet and Rita LeNoble; 5 brothers-in-law: Loy Malliet, Earl Wussow, Jack Bork, Lawrence Wudstrack and Walter Newlun.

The family would like to thank all the staff from the EMT that were very patient, to the ThedaCare Team from New London to Neenah that took excellent care of Carl. Also thank you to the Hospice Care Team, and finally to Dahlke Funeral and Cremation Care from Weyauwega WI, Thank you!

There will be no showing per Carl's wishes.
